<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="189" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,530,1240,1267]" box="[151,530,1240,1267]" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,530,1240,1267]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="189" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,1240,1267]" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">
<taxonomicName box="[151,352,1240,1266]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoleta">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,352,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">Barsine obsoleta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1311,1696]" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">
Members of the group are medium-sized moths with very different wing coloration, but similar male genitalia structure. We include to the group species having the following characteristic features of the male genitalia (
<figureCitation captionStart-0="FIGURES 19 – 21" captionStart-1="FIGURES 22 – 24" captionStartId-0="7.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionStartId-1="8.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox-0="[203,1378,208,1908]" captionTargetBox-1="[193,1388,208,1931]" captionTargetId-0="figure@7.[183,1403,193,1924]" captionTargetId-1="figure@8.[180,1408,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId-0="7" captionTargetPageId-1="8" captionText-0="FIGURES 19 – 21. Barsine spp.: male genitalia. 19, B. obsoleta, neotype, China, Zhejiang, slide AV 1834 m Volynkin; 20, B. callorufa, Taiwan, slide AV 2214 m Volynkin; 21, B. callorufa, holotype, Taiwan, slide TFRI 146149 (photo by Sh. Wu)." captionText-1="FIGURES 22 – 24. Barsine spp.: male genitalia. 22, B. fossi, holotype, Vietnam, Quang Ngai prov., slide AV 1643 m Volynkin; 23, B. striata, China, Zhejiang, slide AV 1864 m Volynkin; 24, B. gratiosa, S India, Nilgiri Hills, slide BMNH (E) Arct- 6493 m Volynkin (© NHM)." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/545873/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/545874/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">Figs. 19–22</figureCitation>
): 1) the distal saccular process without a dorsal lobe (whereas all other known 
<taxonomicName box="[1172,1259,1384,1407]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1172,1259,1384,1407]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">Barsine</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species except 
<taxonomicName authority="Bremer &amp; Grey, 1853" authorityName="Bremer &amp; Grey" authorityYear="1853" box="[151,593,1420,1445]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis box="[151,319,1421,1444]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">Barsine striata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bremer" box="[334,585,1420,1445]" pageId="1" pageNumber="189" refString="Bremer, O. &amp; Grey, W. (1853) Diagnoses de Lepidoptereres nouveaux, trouves par Mm. Tatarinoff et Gaschkewitch aux environs de Pekin in Motschulsky. Etudes entomologiques, 1, 58 - 67." type="journal article" year="1853">Bremer &amp; Grey, 1853</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[609,747,1420,1445]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1489,1512]" captionTargetBox="[199,1392,206,1464]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[180,1408,193,1468]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Barsine spp.: adults. 13, B. gratiosa, male, S India, Nilgiri Hills (© NHM); 14, B. gratiosa, female, S India, Mahableshwar (© NHM); 15, B. mactans, male, E India, Sikkim (ZFMK); 16, B. perlucidula, holotype male, Malay Peninsula, Cameron Highlands (MWM / ZSM); 17, B. striata, male, Russian Far East, Khabarovsk terr. (SZMN); 18, B. striata, female, Russian Far East, Khabarovsk terr. (SZMN)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/545872/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">Figs. 17, 18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[760,790,1420,1444]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[193,1388,208,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[180,1408,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 24. Barsine spp.: male genitalia. 22, B. fossi, holotype, Vietnam, Quang Ngai prov., slide AV 1643 m Volynkin; 23, B. striata, China, Zhejiang, slide AV 1864 m Volynkin; 24, B. gratiosa, S India, Nilgiri Hills, slide BMNH (E) Arct- 6493 m Volynkin (© NHM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/545874/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">23</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[803,832,1420,1444]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 32" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1913,1936]" captionTargetBox="[192,1402,207,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[170,1414,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 32. Barsine spp.: female genitalia. 27, B. obsoleta, China, Zhejiang, slide AV 1835 f Volynkin; 28, B. callorufa, paratype, Taiwan, slide TFRI 145713 (photo by Sh. Wu); 29, B. fossi, paratype, Vietnam, Quang Ngai prov., slide AV 2284 f Volynkin; 30, B. striata, Russian Far East, Khabarovsk terr., slide AV 1781 f Volynkin; 31, B. mactans, E India, Darjeeling, slide AV 1995 f Volynkin; 32, B. gratiosa, S India, Nilgiri Hills, slide BMNH (E) Arct- 6494 f Volynkin (© NHM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/545876/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">30</figureCitation>
) have a dorsal lobe of distal saccular process); 2) 1st medial diverticulum of vesica is long and curved; 3) 2nd medial diverticulum is bilobate, its main lobe is broad and covered with strong short cornuti of different size, and the additional lobe is smaller, conical, with strong scobination. Despite the similarity of the male genital capsules of 
<taxonomicName box="[896,1001,1528,1552]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis box="[896,1001,1528,1552]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">B. striata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the 
<taxonomicName box="[1098,1225,1528,1552]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoleta">
<emphasis box="[1098,1225,1528,1552]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">B. obsoleta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group due to absence of a dorsal lobe of the distal saccular process, the male genital structures of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1208,1336,1564,1588]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoleta">
<emphasis box="[1208,1336,1564,1588]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">B. obsoleta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
speciesgroup are well separated from those of 
<taxonomicName box="[590,694,1600,1624]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis box="[590,694,1600,1624]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">B. striata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the much narrower uncus, the broader apical lobe of valva, and especially the vesica configuration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1168,1671,1696]" pageId="1" pageNumber="189" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1311,1696]" box="[199,1168,1671,1696]" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">
The 
<taxonomicName box="[249,438,1672,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoleta">
<emphasis box="[249,438,1672,1696]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="189">Barsine obsoleta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group includes the three known species reviewed below.
</paragraph>
